18 allow reasonable attorneys' fees to the duly licensed attorneys representing the
19 association obtaining a judgment for damages in said suit, in an amount not to
20 exceed ten thousand dollars ($10,000) or fifteen percent (15%) of the amount
21 recovered, whichever is greater, said attorneys' fees to be taxed as a part of the
22 court costs. When making an award of attorneys' fees under this subdivision,
23 the judge shall issue a written order including findings of fact detailing the
24 factual basis for the finding of an unwarranted refusal to negotiate or pay the
25 debt secured by the claim of lien, and setting forth the amount of the highest
26 offer made by the unit owner 90 days or more before the commencement of
27 trial, and the amount of damages recovered, as well as the factual basis and
28 amount of any such attorneys' fees to be awarded.
29 (3) A unit owner may not be required to pay attorneys' fees and court costs until
30 the unit owner is notified in writing of the association's intent to seek payment
31 of attorneys' fees, costs, and expenses. The notice must be sent by first-class
32 mail to the physical address of the unit and the unit owner's address of record
33 with the association and, if different, to the address for the unit owner shown
34 on the county tax records for the unit. The association must make reasonable
35 and diligent efforts to ensure that its records contain the unit owner's current
36 mailing address. Notwithstanding anything to the contrary in this Chapter,
37 there shall be no requirement that notice under this subsection be mailed to an
38 address which is known to be a vacant unit or a unit for which there is no
39 United States postal address. The notice shall set out the outstanding balance
40 due as of the date of the notice and state that the unit owner has 15 days from
41 the mailing of the notice by first-class mail to pay the outstanding balance
42 without the attorneys' fees and court costs. If the unit owner pays the
43 outstanding balance within this period, then the unit owner shall have no
44 obligation to pay attorneys' fees, costs, or expenses. The notice shall also
45 inform the unit owner of the opportunity to contact a representative of the
46 association to discuss a payment schedule for the outstanding balance as
47 provided in subsection (i) of this section and shall provide the name and
48 telephone number of the representative.
