28 SECTION 7. G.S. 47C-3-118 reads as rewritten:
29 "§ 47C-3-118. Association records.
30 (a) The association shall keep financial records sufficiently detailed to enable the
31 association to comply with this chapter. All financial and other records, including records of
32 meetings of the association and executive board, shall be made reasonably available for
33 examination by any unit owner and the unit owner's authorized agents as required by the bylaws
34 and by Chapter 55A of the General Statutes if the association is a nonprofit corporation. If the
35 bylaws do not specify a shorter time, the association shall make the requested records reasonably
36 available for examination within 30 days of receiving the unit owner's written request. Except as
37 otherwise provided in the bylaws, the association is not required to make available for
38 examination financial records created more than three years before the date on which the
39 association receives the unit owner's written request. If the bylaws do not specify particular
40 records to be maintained, the association shall keep accurate records of all cash receipts and
41 expenditures and all assets and liabilities. In addition to any specific information that is required
42 by the bylaws to be assembled and reported to the unit owners at specified times, the association
43 shall make an annual income and expense statement and balance sheet available to all unit owners
44 at no charge and within 75 days after the close of the fiscal year to which the information relates.
45 Notwithstanding the bylaws, a more extensive compilation, review, or audit of the association's
46 books and records for the current or immediately preceding fiscal year may be required by a vote
47 of the majority of the executive board or by the affirmative vote of a majority of the unit owners
48 present and voting in person or by proxy at any annual meeting or any special meeting duly called
49 for that purpose.
50 (a1) A unit owner or the unit owner's authorized agent is entitled to inspect and copy, at a
51 reasonable time and location specified by the association, any contract entered into by the
