5 SECTION 11. G.S. 47F-3-118 reads as rewritten:
6 "§ 47F-3-118. Association records.
7 (a) The association shall keep financial records sufficiently detailed to enable the
8 association to comply with this Chapter. All financial and other records, including records of
9 meetings of the association and executive board, shall be made reasonably available for
10 examination by any lot owner and the lot owner's authorized agents as required in the bylaws and
11 Chapter 55A of the General Statutes. If the bylaws do not specify a shorter time, the association
12 shall make records reasonably available for examination within 30 days of receiving the lot
13 owner's written request. Except as otherwise provided in the bylaws, the association is not
14 required to make available for examination financial records created more than three years before
15 the date on which the association receives the lot owner's written request. If the bylaws do not
16 specify particular records to be maintained, the association shall keep accurate records of all cash
17 receipts and expenditures and all assets and liabilities. In addition to any specific information
18 that is required by the bylaws to be assembled and reported to the lot owners at specified times,
19 the association shall make an annual income and expense statement and balance sheet available
20 to all lot owners at no charge and within 75 days after the close of the fiscal year to which the
21 information relates. Notwithstanding the bylaws, a more extensive compilation, review, or audit
22 of the association's books and records for the current or immediately preceding fiscal year may
23 be required by a vote of the majority of the executive board or by the affirmative vote of a
24 majority of the lot owners present and voting in person or by proxy at any annual meeting or any
25 special meeting duly called for that purpose.
26 (a1) A lot owner or the lot owner's authorized agent is entitled to inspect and copy, at a
27 reasonable time and location specified by the association, any contract entered into by the
28 association authorizing a managing agent to exercise any of the powers granted to the association
29 pursuant to G.S. 47F-3-102 if the lot owner gives the association written notice of the demand at
30 least five business days before the date on which the lot owner wishes to inspect and copy and
31 the request satisfies the conditions for inspection set forth in G.S. 55A-16-02(c). A demand to
32 inspect made pursuant to this subsection shall be presumed to have been made in good faith and
33 for a proper purpose. In any action to compel the inspection and copying of documents, the court
34 may award reasonable attorneys' fees to the prevailing party. If the association does not allow a
35 lot owner who complies with this subsection to inspect and copy the requested contract, and, if a
36 court of competent jurisdiction thereafter enters an order compelling the association to do so, the
37 court shall also order the association to pay the lot owner's costs, including reasonable attorneys'
38 fees, incurred to obtain the order.
